Class AckMessage

  • java.lang.Object
    • Message
      • AckMessage
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public final class AckMessage
extends Message
    This message type is used to acknowledge chunks in the transfer. If the transfer must be stopped or cannot be started, the server responds with an AckMessage of sequence number -1.

    The sequence number in the ACK is for the next expected chunk. For example, if the server accepts chunk 17, it will send ACK 18. When the server has accepted all chunks, it sends ACK N where N is the number of chunks in the transfer.

    When a server receives a chunk but cannot accept it, it sends a repeated ACK (the last ACK is sent again). For example, if the next chunk is 17 but the CRC is bad, the server will send ACK 17 again instead of ACK 18 and wait for a retransmission of the previous chunk.
